      "memo": "Preferred cloud partnerships give the processor pricing advantages on compute that further widen the gap between the processor's value capture and the data provider's input.",
      "detail": "Cloud pricing discounts through preferred partnerships reduce the processor's cost of recursive derivation. Lower compute costs make additional derivation rounds economically attractive. The data provider's input price was set without knowledge of the processor's cloud economics. Preferred-partner compute pricing is an invisible factor that makes recursive value extraction more profitable for the processor."
    },
