      "memo": "Enterprise-grade security protects the processor's recursive pipeline and derived datasets from competitors but does not give the data provider visibility into the pipeline.",
      "detail": "Security protects the processor's derived assets, including the recursively generated training data. Enterprise-grade security means the processor's competitive advantage in recursive value capture is protected from rivals. However, this security also prevents the data provider from auditing the recursive pipeline. Security serves the processor's interests in both directions: protecting derived value and obscuring its creation."
    },
    "Adversary Model": {
