      "memo": "Model weights containing recursively derived value may be copyable or transferable, meaning the recursive value extracted from data providers can proliferate beyond the original processor.",
      "detail": "If model weights are copyable, the recursively captured value can be transferred to parties who never contracted with the original data provider. Weight copying multiplies the pricing failure: value extracted through recursion can be redistributed without any payment flowing back to data providers. Copyable weights mean recursive pricing failure is not contained to the original processor-provider relationship."
    },
    "Access Control": {
