    "Data Value Dynamics": {
      "value": "Elastic/synthetic",
      "memo": "Recursive derivation creates elastic value by generating synthetic training data from licensed inputs, stretching the original data's contribution far beyond its contracted price.",
      "detail": "Each recursive round produces synthetic derived data that extends the original data's influence. The elasticity is one-directional: value expands for the processor while the data provider's price remains fixed. Synthetic data generated through recursion may partially substitute for new licensed data, reducing the processor's future data procurement needs. Elasticity means the original data's value to the processor grows while its price does not."
